    * updated for new RPM which does not accept some old tags
    * updated for new GT system and drivers
  * doc/gtapi.txt
  * source/rtl/accept.c
  * source/rtl/alert.c
  * source/rtl/console.c
  * source/rtl/gx.c
  * source/rtl/set.c
  * source/rtl/xsavescr.c
  * source/vm/hvm.c
    * updated for new GT system and drivers
  * include/Makefile
  * include/hbextern.ch
  + include/hbgtcore.h
  * include/hbapigt.h
  - include/gfx.ch
  - include/gfxtrans.ch
  + include/hbgfx.ch
  + include/hbgfxdef.ch
    * new GTAPI
      hbgtcore.h file should not be included by user code
      it's only for internal use in GT drivers
    * HB_inkey_enum changed to int - this is bit field not enumerated type.
      Many of C/C++ compilers forbid bit operations on enum types and
      forcing it by casting which finally exceeds the enum range is defined
      as bug because it may badly interacts with some compiler optimizations
  * include/inkey.ch
  * include/hbapi.h
  * include/hbset.h
  + include/hbwince.h
  * include/hbdefs.h
  * source/common/hbver.c
  * source/ct/Makefile
  + source/ct/ctwfunc.c
  * source/ct/ctwin.c
  + source/ct/ctwin.h
  + source/ct/cursor.c
  - source/ct/dattime3.prg
  + source/ct/dattime3.c
  - source/ct/invrtwin.prg
