2008-03-10 14:25 UTC+0300 Phil Krylov <phil a t newstar.rinet.ru>
  * doc/en/set.txt
  * include/set.ch
  * include/hbset.h
  * source/rtl/set.c
    + New SET value named _SET_EOF. Defaults to FALSE on UN*X, but defaults
      to TRUE on everything else. If set to FALSE, then CHR(26) does not get
      written when closing any of the various text files that are created
      using various SET values.
  (by David G. Holm, borrowed from Harbour)

